# HCMUS GPA Rules

- UI copy for students must be Vietnamese with accents, warm, natural and non-technical.
- Keep implementation identifiers, database keys and enum values ASCII.
- Prefer Server Components for route data; keep client components as focused interaction leaves.
- Authenticate all server mutations and rely on Supabase RLS for user-owned rows.
- Do not create parallel mutation paths for the same feature; API routes and future Server Actions must delegate to shared data logic.
- GPA is calculated from effective course attempts only; attempts preserve retake and improvement history.
- GPA hệ 10 is stored and displayed with three decimal places; GPA hệ 4 stays two decimal places.
- Search over curriculum text must be accent-insensitive.
- Motion must communicate state or guide attention, use opacity/transform/SVG stroke, and respect `prefers-reduced-motion`.
- Avoid exposing implementation terms such as schema, seed, SSR, production or Supabase in student-facing screens unless it is an error meant for developers.
